<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">
This species is easily recognizable by the orange elytra without maculation. The only species similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. bipartita" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="bipartita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">B. bipartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. westwoodii" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="westwoodii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">B. westwoodii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. westwoodii" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="westwoodii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">B. westwoodii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much larger and has the pronotum almost entirely orange with only a basal black macula (
<bibRefCitation author="Nestor-Arriola, JI" journalOrPublisher="Entomologia Mexicana" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" pagination="824 - 830" refId="B23" refString="Nestor-Arriola, JI, Toledo-Hernandez, VH, 2016. Revision de las especies del genero Brachiacantha Dejean, 1837, (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) pertenecientes al grupo 3 de Leng. Entomologia Mexicana 3: 824 - 830" title="Revision de las especies del genero Brachiacantha Dejean, 1837, (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) pertenecientes al grupo 3 de Leng." volume="3" year="2016">
Nestor-Arriola and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Toledo-Hernández">Toledo-Hernandez</normalizedToken>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). The material was identified following the description of 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.8953" author="Mulsant, ME" journalOrPublisher="Annales des Sciences Physiques et Naturelles, d'agriculture et d'industrie Lyon" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" pagination="1 - 1104" refId="B22" refString="Mulsant, ME, 1850. Species de Coleopteres trimeres securipalpes. Annales des Sciences Physiques et Naturelles, d'agriculture et d'industrie Lyon 2: 1 - 1104, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.8953" title="Species de Coleopteres trimeres securipalpes." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.8953" volume="2" year="1850">Mulsant (1850)</bibRefCitation>
and considering the information of 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/187631289X00366" author="Booth, RG" journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" pagination="343 - 370" refId="B2" refString="Booth, RG, Pope, RD, 1989. A review of the type material of Coccinellidae (Coleoptera) described by F.W. Hope, and by E. Mulsant in the Hope Entomological Collections, Oxford. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 20 (3): 343 - 370, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/187631289X00366" title="A review of the type material of Coccinellidae (Coleoptera) described by F. W. Hope, and by E. Mulsant in the Hope Entomological Collections, Oxford." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/187631289X00366" volume="20" year="1989">Booth and Pope (1989)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
